{
  "doc_id": "52631",
  "text": "A number of studies have suggested that deglycosylation can affect HIV-1 envelope antigenicity and immunogenicity [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] [CITATION_10] [CITATION_11] . A non-glycosylated outer domain of gp120 has been reported to be immunogenic and induce weak neutralizing antibodies in rabbits [CITATION_12] . For example, loss of sialic acids on gp120 has been reported to improve Env immunogenicity [CITATION_13] [CITATION_14] . Strategies for native deglycosylation of Env have been described that can improve both immunogenicity and sensitivity of resulting virions to neutralization [CITATION_15] [CITATION_16] .",
